args: There are an unusual number of couples\nwalking about town today.
Do you think they're all out celebrating\nDragonyule?
Perhaps. Regardless, they all seem to be\nenjoying themselves; I don't believe\nSaint Starfall's support is needed here.
Wait. Look at that man there.
Ah, but he does appear to be in low spirits.\nMy assistance is needed after all!
Ho there, plebeian! Tell Saint Starfall what\nis troubling you, that he might resolve it!
Heh, really? Thanks, but no one can\nhelp with this.
Ha HA! You could not be more wrong!\nNothing is impossible for me!
Easy, Xander. ...Sir, if you don't mind\ntalking to us, you'd probably feel better\ngetting your worries off your chest.
Oh, I suppose you're right. In that case,\nthe problem is with a girl I like.
She's come into my shop a few times,\nbut she also happens to be the daughter\nof a wealthy noble.
But she's not haughty or arrogant at all!\nShe always takes a moment to smile at\nme and pass the time with conversation.
A sure sign she cares for you! Do you\nnot agree, {player_name}?
Aren't you maybe reading a bit too\nmuch into that actual—
Nonsense! The woman is clearly waiting\nfor you to declare your undying love!
In which case, I shall create a situation\nwhere you might confess your feelings!
Er, but she's a noble. I can't just walk\nup to her and start a conversation.
Ha HA! You are speaking to a king, lad!\nNo door is barred to me!
Halt! Who goes there? This is off-limits!
Mind your tongue, knave! You speak\nto Xander—and Saint Starfall besides!

Now see here! You must have spoken with
many a noble in your lowly position as
gatekeeper, yes? Surely you can tell that
I have the aura of royalty!
Actually, he IS a king. ...And I'm a prince,\nif that makes any difference.
Well, this is JUST what I needed today.\nI'm probably going to get sacked no matter\nwhat I end up deciding...
I'm glad you finally understand.\nThen inside we shall go! Ha HA!
Whoa. He actually let us through.
It's too early to be celebrating, dear lad.\nThe real ordeal is yet to come.
A-ha! Is that the object of your affections?
Th-that's her. Oh man, all of this is\nmaking my stomach hurt...
Have courage, young man, and go forth\nsafe in the knowledge that we both are\nwatching over you!
Hmm? Oh, hello! You work at that shop\nin the village, right?
That's right! Er, a-and I'm so happy that\nyou remember me!
But the thing is... Well, you see,\nI really came here to tell you something...
Hmm? You there! Leave my daughter\nalone and depart from this place at once!
Please wait, Father. He says he came here\nto tell me something.
And what subject of worth could a\ncommoner POSSIBLY have to discuss\nwith nobles such as ourselves?
This is not a matter of class, sir!
This moment will determine the course of\nthat young man's future; you must stand\naside and let it unfold as it will.
Hmph! Now I see what is going on...\nand it is all the more reason he must\nleave at once!
No commoner has the right to confess\ntheir love to a noble. How absurd!
You are no more noble than he to the eyes\nof a king like myself!
Now be silent and let him speak!
Go on, young man. Tell that woman\nthe strength of your love for her!
See, the thing is, ever since I first met\nyou, I've...
...Sorry it had to end like that.
I never expected she might refuse him!\nStill, this IS a positive outcome\nin its own way.
How could having his love rejected\nbe a positive outcome?
He was able to see his resolve through to\nthe end. The result is purely secondary.
I expect you feel the same way,\nyoung man?
Sort of, I guess. I mean, I'm sad she said\nno, but I DO feel a lot better now that it's\nout in the open.
So thank you. If you two hadn't come when\nyou did, I'd have been agonizing over what\nto do forever.
So what matters is not having regrets?\nI see. That makes sense.
Indeed. I shall kick down the walls around\nthe heart and liberate it. Thus is the\nsacred task and duty of Saint Starfall!

Stars are as beautiful when they fall as
they are when they shine high in the sky.
So go forth, young man, and turn the next
page of your life!
